<p>A Life in the Theatre is a 1977 play by <ref target="/wiki/David_Mamet" title="David Mamet">David Mamet</ref>.</p>
<p>It focuses on the relationship between two actors, the play's only characters. One, Robert, is a stage veteran while John is a young, promising actor. As the play goes on they are involved in a variety of productions, and gradually their relationship begins to change.</p>

